detaileddescription.para:
Type: INFORMATIONAL
Cause:
This event message is issued when the CFS Health and Safety has completed initialization.
The Version fields contain the HS_MAJOR_VERSION, HS_MINOR_VERSION, HS_REVISION, and HS_MISSION_REV version identifiers.

Type: CRITICAL
Cause:
This event message is issued when CFS Health and Safety exits due to a fatal error condition.
The err field contains the return status from the cFE call that caused the app to terminate

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when a software bus message is received with an invalid command code.
The ID field contains the message ID, the CC field contains the command code that generated the error.

Cause:
This event message is issued when a software bus message is received with an invalid message ID.
The message ID field contains the message ID that generated the error.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when a housekeeping request is received with a message length that doesn't match the expected value.

The ID field contains the message ID, the CC field contains the command code, the Len field is the actual length returned by the CFE_SB_GetTotalMsgLength call, and the Expected field is the expected length for the message.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when a ground command message is received with a message length that doesn't match the expected value.

The ID field contains the message ID, the CC field contains the command code, the Len field is the actual length returned by the CFE_SB_GetTotalMsgLength call, and the Expected field is the expected length for a message with that command code.

'Processor Reset Action Limit Reached: No Reset Performed'

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when the action specified by an Application or Event monitor that fails is Processor Reset, and no more Processor Resets are allowed.

para.computeroutput: 'App Monitor App Name not found: APP:(%s)'
'App Monitor App Name not found: APP:(%s)'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when an application name cannot be resolved into an application ID by the OS.
The APP field specifies the name in the table that was not found in the system.

para.computeroutput: 'App Monitor Failure: APP:(%s): Action: Restart Application'
'App Monitor Failure: APP:(%s): Action: Restart Application'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when a monitored application fails to increment its execution counter in the table specified number of cycles, and the specified action type is Application Restart.
The APP field specifies the name of the application that failed to check in.

para.computeroutput: 'Call to Restart App Failed: APP:(%s) ERR: 0x%08X'
'Call to Restart App Failed: APP:(%s) ERR: 0x%08X'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when the app monitor attempts to restart a task and is unable to.

The APP field is the name of the application that was being restarted The ERR field is the return code from the CFE_ES_RestartApp or CFE_ES_GetAppInfo or CFE_ES_GetAppIDByName function call that generated the error.

para.computeroutput: 'App Monitor Failure: APP:(%s): Action: Event Only'
'App Monitor Failure: APP:(%s): Action: Event Only'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when a monitored application fails to increment its execution counter in the table specified number of cycles, and the specified action type is Event Only.
The APP field specifies the name of the application that failed to check in.

para.computeroutput: 'App Monitor Failure: APP:(%s): Action: Processor Reset'
'App Monitor Failure: APP:(%s): Action: Processor Reset'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when a monitored application fails to increment its execution counter in the table specified number of cycles, and the specified action type is Processor Reset.
The APP field specifies the name of the application that failed to check in.

para.computeroutput: 'App Monitor Failure: APP:(%s): Action: Message Action Index: %d'
'App Monitor Failure: APP:(%s): Action: Message Action Index: %d'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when a monitored application fails to increment its execution counter in the table specified number of cycles, and the specified action type is a Message Action.
The APP field specifies the name of the application that failed to check in. The Message Action Index specifies the message action number.

para.computeroutput: 'Event Monitor: APP:(%s) EID:(%d): Action: Message Action Index: %d'
'Event Monitor: APP:(%s) EID:(%d): Action: Message Action Index: %d'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when a monitored event is detected, and the specified action type is a Message Action.
The APP field specifies the name of the application that sent the message. The EID field specifies the event ID in the message. The Message Action Index specifies the message action number.

para.computeroutput: 'Event Monitor: APP:(%s) EID:(%d): Action: Processor Reset'
'Event Monitor: APP:(%s) EID:(%d): Action: Processor Reset'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when an event is received that matches an event in the event monitor table that specifies Processor Reset as the action type
The APP field specifies the name of the application that issued the event and is being restarted. TheEID specifies the event ID of that message.

para.computeroutput: 'Event Monitor: APP:(%s) EID:(%d): Action: Restart Application'
'Event Monitor: APP:(%s) EID:(%d): Action: Restart Application'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when an event is received that matches an event in the event monitor table that specifies Restart Application as the action type
The APP field specifies the name of the application that issued the event and is being restarted. TheEID specifies the event ID of that message.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when the event monitor attempts to restart a task and is unable to.
The APP field is the name of the application that was being restarted The ERR field is the return code from the CFE_ES_RestartApp function call that generated the error.

Cause:

para.computeroutput: 'Call to Delete App Failed: APP:(%s) ERR: 0x%08X'
'Call to Delete App Failed: APP:(%s) ERR: 0x%08X'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when the event monitor attempts to delete a task and is unable to.
The APP field is the name of the application that was being deleted The ERR field is the return code from the CFE_ES_DeleteApp function call that generated the error.

Type: INFORMATIONAL
Cause:
This event message is issued when a table validation has been completed for an application monitor table load
The good field is number of entries that passed. The bad field is number of entries that failed. The unused field is the number of entries that weren't checked because they were marked unused.

para.computeroutput: 'AppMon verify err: Entry = %d, Err = %d, Action = %d, App = %s'
'AppMon verify err: Entry = %d, Err = %d, Action = %d, App = %s'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued on the first error when a table validation fails for a application monitor table load.

The Entry field is the number of the application monitor table entry. The Err field is the error id of the error that occurred. The Action field is the action listed for the entry. The App is field the application name specified in the table.

Type: INFORMATIONAL
Cause:
This event message is issued when a table validation has been completed for an event monitor table load
The good field is number of entries that passed. The bad field is number of entries that failed. The unused field is the number of entries that weren't checked because they were marked unused.

para.computeroutput: 'EventMon verify err: Entry = %d, Err = %d, Action = %d, ID = %d App = %s'
'EventMon verify err: Entry = %d, Err = %d, Action = %d, ID = %d App = %s'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued on the first error when a table validation fails for an event monitor table load.

The Entry field is the number of the event monitor table entry. The Err field is the error id of the error that occurred. The Action field is the action listed for the entry. The ID field is the Event ID listed in the table. The App is field the application name specified in the table.

Type: INFORMATIONAL
Cause:
This event message is issued when a table validation has been completed for an execution counters table load
The good field is number of entries that passed. The bad field is number of entries that failed. The unused field is the number of entries that weren't checked because they were marked unused.

para.computeroutput: 'ExeCount verify err: Entry = %d, Err = %d, Type = %d, Name = %s'
'ExeCount verify err: Entry = %d, Err = %d, Type = %d, Name = %s'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued on the first error when a table validation fails for an execution counter table load.

The Entry field is the number of the execution counter table entry. The Err field is the error id of the error that occurred. The Type field is the resource type for the entry. The Name is field the resource name specified in the table.

Type: INFORMATIONAL
Cause:
This event message is issued when a table validation has been completed for an message actions table load
The good field is number of entries that passed. The bad field is number of entries that failed. The unused field is the number of entries that weren't checked because they were marked unused.

para.computeroutput: 'MsgActs verify err: Entry = %d, Err = %d, Length = %d, ID = %d'
'MsgActs verify err: Entry = %d, Err = %d, Length = %d, ID = %d'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued on the first error when a table validation fails for an message actions table load.

The Entry field is the number of the message action table entry. The Err field is the error id of the error that occurred. The Length field is the length of the message. The ID field is the Message ID of the message.

para.computeroutput: 'Event Monitor Enable: Error Subscribing to Events,RC=0x%08X'
'Event Monitor Enable: Error Subscribing to Events,RC=0x%08X'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when a ground command message is received to enable event monitoring while it is disabled, and there is an error subscribing to the event mid.
The Status field indicates the error status passed but the subscribe call.

para.computeroutput: 'Event Monitor Disable: Error Unsubscribing from Events,RC=0x%08X'
'Event Monitor Disable: Error Unsubscribing from Events,RC=0x%08X'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when a ground command message is received to disable event monitoring while it is enabled, and there is an error unsubscribing from the event mid.
The Status field indicates the error status passed but the subscribe call.

Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued if when acquiring the event monitor table from table services, it is bad and event monitoring is disabled, but there is a failure unsubscribing from the event mid.
The Status field indicates the error status passed but the subscribe call.
